  <p>In order to mitigate the spread of COVID-19 in the country, on 30<sup>th</sup>, March 2020, the General Health Council,
    headed by the President of Mexico, decreed a state of national sanitary emergency due to force majeure; therefore it was
    agreed to suspend non-essential activities throughout all the states, which includes the construction of housing.</p>

  <p>Nevertheless, this contingency is leading to the deployment of counter-cyclical measures to encourage the sale of real
    estate inventory as economic activity begins to normalize (through mortgage loans with lower interest rates, as well as
    joint financing schemes, such as those launched by Infonavit and Fovissste).</p>

